            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the linguine<strong> </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until the spinach has wilted, then drain, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong>, and return to the pot</p><p>Once the tomato<strong> </strong>sauce has thickened, add the <strong>drained linguine & spinach </strong>to the pan with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp [1 1/2 tsp] [2 tsp]<strong> sugar</strong>, a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until the linguine is coated in the sauce – this is your <strong>tangy tomato & chicken linguine</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
